text:
I'd like to add a random quote to my site, ideally another random quote would be selected during each page reload. I tried to do this with an `hfun_`:

```&lt;!-- HTML --&gt;
&lt;p style="font-style: italic;"&gt;
    {{randomquote}}
&lt;/p&gt;

---------------------------------
# Julia
function hfun_randomquote()
  facts = [
    "fact1",
    "fact2",
    "fact3"
  ] 

  return rand(facts)
end```
This does populate the random quote field in the html, but it does not change on reload (locally on my computer). Is there any way to run custom code on page reload?
